alert.note: Alert for Humboldt County (Nevada) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued March 08 at 1:49PM PST until March 11 at 1:00AM PST by NWS Elko
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 PM THURSDAY TO 10 AM PST FRIDAY... ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM FRIDAY TO 1 AM PST SATURDAY... * WHAT...For the High Wind Warning, southwest winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 70 mph expected. For the Wind Advisory, south winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected. * WHERE...Humboldt County. * WHEN...For the High Wind Warning, from 10 AM Friday to 1 AM PST Saturday. For the Wind Advisory, from 10 PM Thursday to 10 AM PST Friday. * IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind.
